places, including bridges, mills and dams. However, because of their clandestine nature, these deeds of "derring-do" have not been studied in any detail, a major gap which this book fills. It surveys a wide variety of special operations, from the eleventh to the sixteenth century. It then analyzes in greater depth six select and exciting operations: the betrayal of Antioch in 1098; the attempt to rescue King Baldwin II from the dungeon of Khartpert in 1123; the assassination of Conrad of Montferrat in 1192; the attempt to storm Calais in 1350; the "dirty war" waged by the rulers of France and Burgundy in the 1460s and 1470s; and the demolition of the flour mill of Auriol in 1536. Professor YUVAL NOAH HARARI teaches at the Hebrew University of Jerusalem, and is the author of the international bestseller Sapiens: A Brief History of Humankind.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEspionage -- History -- To 1500. 0aMiddle Ages. 0aMilitary history, Medieval. 0aSpecial operations (Military science) -- History. 4aMedieval History. 4aMilitary History. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aA Brief History of Humankind.  aA Brief History of Tomorrow.  aHarari.  aHomo Deus.  aSapiens.  aSpecial Operations.  aYuval Noah Harari.  aauthor of Sapiens.  amedieval military history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781846155949?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781846155949423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781846155949/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles